cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the transmission dynamics of online social contagion. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it uses mathematical models to study social phenomena. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) as it deals with the spread of online infections. The paper also involves data analysis and statistical modelling, which could place it under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
